It can be seen from Fig. 8 that both mean and variance of the beta distribution increase as the IFR increases. The corresponding dynamics are shown in Fig. 9. The normalised numbers of individuals decrease as the IFR increases, because the observations are divided by the median of the beta distribution which is increasing with the IFR. The width of the prediction intervals also decreases as the IFR increases. The filtered dynamics well reconstruct the behaviour of the adjusted data in all the cases. The estimated parameters \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
