A statistical model, belonging to a parametric family, is said to be identifiable if, for any two different values of parameters, there exists at least a measurable set in the sample space that is not assigned the same probability by the two members of the family, that is, given \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\theta _{01}\ne \theta _{02}$$\end{document}θ01≠θ02, there exists at least one set B such that24\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \Pr (Y_{1:t}\in B;\theta _{01})\ne \Pr (Y_{1:t}{} \mathbf \in B;\theta _{02}) \ , \end{aligned}$$\end{document}Pr(Y1:t∈B;θ01)≠Pr(Y1:t∈B;θ02),where \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Y_{1:t}$$\end{document}Y1:t denotes a finite-length trajectory of observations from (7). For a deterministic model, this property is called structural identifiability, which holds if there exists a map from the parameter to the output \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\theta _0 \mapsto y_{1:t}(\theta _0)$$\end{document}θ0↦y1:t(θ0) which is injective, that is, given \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\theta _{01}\ne \theta _{02}$$\end{document}θ01≠θ02, the two models \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
